  <compounddef id="ERROR" kind="page">
    <compoundname>ERROR</compoundname>
    <title>ERROR Keyword</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">ERROR<sp/>string-expression</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Raises a <bold>runtime error</bold>.</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Sets the built-in variables <bold>ERR$</bold> (to the message) and <bold>ERR</bold> (to <computeroutput>1</computeroutput>) <bold>when</bold>:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>the error is raised <bold>inside</bold> an <ref refid="EVAL" kindref="compound">EVAL</ref>, <bold>or</bold></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>an error handler has been installed with <ulink url="https://github.com/brainboxdotcc/retro-rocket/wiki/ONERROR"><computeroutput>ON ERROR</computeroutput></ulink>.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>If <bold>no</bold> handler is installed and you are not inside <computeroutput>EVAL</computeroutput>, the program <bold>terminates</bold>.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="remark"><para><computeroutput>ERR</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>ERR$</computeroutput> are described on the </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="remark"><para><ref refid="variables" kindref="compound">Variable Types</ref> page.</para>
</simplesect>
<hruler/>
</para>
<sect3 id="ERROR_1autotoc_md754">
<title>Examples</title>
<para><bold>Uncaught error (program terminates)</bold></para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>&quot;About<sp/>to<sp/>fail...&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">ERROR<sp/>&quot;there<sp/>are<sp/>owls<sp/>loose&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>&quot;This<sp/>line<sp/>is<sp/>never<sp/>reached&quot;</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><bold>Caught error with <computeroutput>ON ERROR PROC...</computeroutput></bold></para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">ON<sp/>ERROR<sp/>PROCerr_handler</highlight></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>&quot;Doing<sp/>a<sp/>risky<sp/>thing...&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">ERROR<sp/>&quot;there<sp/>are<sp/>owls<sp/>loose&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>&quot;Carrying<sp/>on<sp/>after<sp/>handler&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">END</highlight></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">DEF<sp/>PROCerr_handler</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>PRINT<sp/>&quot;ERROR:<sp/>&quot;;<sp/>ERR$</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>PRINT<sp/>&quot;ERR<sp/>code:<sp/>&quot;;<sp/>ERR</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">ENDPROC</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>In this example, the handler runs, <computeroutput>ERR$</computeroutput> contains the message, and <computeroutput>ERR</computeroutput> is <computeroutput>1</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect3>
<sect3 id="ERROR_1autotoc_md756">
<title>Notes</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><computeroutput>ERROR</computeroutput> accepts a <bold>string expression</bold>; use it to describe the failure clearly.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>ON ERROR</computeroutput> supports only <computeroutput>ON ERROR PROCname</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>ON ERROR OFF</computeroutput>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>When raised inside <computeroutput>EVAL</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>ERR</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>ERR$</computeroutput> are set; see the <computeroutput>EVAL</computeroutput> page for how control returns to the caller.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><bold>See also:</bold> <linebreak/>
